  "doc_id": "464",
  "text": "Depending on where we focus our attention during a situation, we may be more apt to notice or miss particular elements of that scene. For instance, focusing on how many passes white-jerseyed players make in a basketball game results in many individuals failing to notice a gorilla walking amongst the players [CITATION_1] . Likewise, students engaging in a cell phone conversation seemed to miss money hanging from a tree, even when they had to actively avoid running right into it [CITATION_2] . What would cause a person to miss things that seem so obvious? An explanation may be found in the phenomenon known as \"inattentional blindness.\"",
